    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3399: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fuller</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-18T00:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1920—midnight</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 19—7:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Japanese interference radio to Peking has now ceased. Railways again blocked, but
                    by railway wrecks. Chihli troops continue receiving heavy reenforcements. Tuan
                    troops still retreating toward Peking. My position [at] all consular body
                    meetings has been to prevent any possible action which might be construed as
                    favoring either faction. All quiet at Tientsin, British Admiralty Admiral
                    arrived today, also two Japanese destroyers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fuller</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
